<item>
            <title>[LU-17788] restore ptlrpc watchdog timer message</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17788</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The patch &lt;a href=&quot;https://review.whamcloud.com/33018&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://review.whamcloud.com/33018&lt;/a&gt; &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9859&quot; title=&quot;libcfs simplification&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-9859&quot;&gt;LU-9859&lt;/a&gt; libcfs: add watchdog for ptlrpc service threads&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; removed important debugging information for MDS and OSS service threads that become stuck processing some request.  The message that reports the threads &lt;b&gt;later become unstuck&lt;/b&gt; was lost, so it isn&apos;t clear that the threads have continued on to process other requests.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Restore those messages.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
